{
  "text": "Now we'll create a launch template for our web servers. We're using the latest Amazon Linux 2023 AMI, which is optimized for AWS. The template specifies a T3.micro instance type, which is eligible for the free tier. We attach the web security group we created earlier and the IAM instance profile for secure AWS access. The user data script installs and starts a simple web server. Notice how we're using the latest AMI lookup. This ensures we always get the most recent patched version. The template is all tilted towards some new curly race. We would switch it to the app that we're using.",
